      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHASING RAINBOWS (2) started at big odds on debut but ran a bold race, finishing second beaten 2 lengths over 1200m at Pakenham. Has been well educated and has plenty of improvement in store. ARADEO (1) found the line nicely to grab second beaten just a half-length over 1200m at Ararat. Raced a $2.9F building on a solid debut placing at Sale. Has been freshened and kept up to the mark with a Pakenham jumpout. In a top metro barn and will keep improving. ZEPHYR SONG (7) resumes, and as with the above pair, is in good hands. Placed at Seymour before the spell and has looked sharp in two recent Flemington jumpouts. She will jump and run from the inside barrier and will be naturally improved. RACE FOR RULE (5) has been well prepared for her debut outing. The Magnus filly is worth a betting watch.",
